	<item>
				<title>Postcard from Kyoto and Osaka</title>
		<link>http://www.phwl.org/blog/postcard-from-kyoto-and-osaka/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 19 Dec 2013 04:22:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[phwl]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.phwl.org/blog/?p=1191</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Following the <a href="http://www.icfpt.org">International Conference on Field Programmable Technology</a> we spent some time in Kyoto and Osaka.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123566.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1259" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123566-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

<!--more-->

Clear Water Temple is a World Heritage Site. Here are some schoolgirls playing with water.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123659.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1218" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123659-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Prayer cards.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123629.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1217" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123629-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Nice hat.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123575.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1216" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123575-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

This is Clear Water Temple itself, with a view of Kyoto in the background. Built in 1633, it is a magnificent piece of carpentry.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123664.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1226" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123664-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a><a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/clearwatertemple.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1215" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/clearwatertemple-1024x424.jpg" width="584" height="241" /></a>

Massive pieces of timber were used and lots of fancy joints.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123590.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1227" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123590-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a><a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123628.jpg"><img alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123628-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

This picture is actually quite misleading as autumn was long over.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123668.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1220" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123668-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>A beautiful garden.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123671.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1210" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123671-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

We then took the bus to nearby Gion.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123779.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1214" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123779-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Many tourists enjoy dressing up in kimonos and taking selfies.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123757.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1213" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123757-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Japanese marbled beef restaurant.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123780.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1233" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123780-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123809.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1238" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123809-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a><a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123784.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1234" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123784-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>  <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123796.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1236" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123796-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

The Shinto Fushimi Inari Shrine with many torii gates.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123748.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1212" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC123748-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Of all the places we visited, I was most impressed by Nijo Castle and its surrounding gardens.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133982.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1209" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133982-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133977.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1208" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133977-1024x694.jpg" width="584" height="395" /></a>

A serious mortise and tenon.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133959.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1228" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133959-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Nishiki market.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133839.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1230" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133839-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a> <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133938.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1231" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133938-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

A simple breakfast.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133859.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1232" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133859-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Japanese knives are only ground on one side (chisel grind) and hence are either left or right handed. This was part of the left handed offerings.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133884.jpg"><img alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133884-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Sharpening bench.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133891.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1247" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133891-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Not sure if he is applying his maker's stamp here.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133898.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1248" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133898-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>  <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133903.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1250" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC133903-1024x670.jpg" width="584" height="382" /></a>

We then went to a ryokan on Lake Biwa, the largest freshwater lake in Japan,<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC144095.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1204" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC144095-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

and played camping.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC144143.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1219" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC144143-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

A private spa in the ryokan.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154157.jpg"><img alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154157-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

&nbsp;

A bit of a feast with Japanese marbled beef, sashimi and crab.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC144121.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1251" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC144121-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Following the visit to Lake Biwa, we went to Kyoto station and took the train to Osaka.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC144082.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1203" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC144082-768x1024.jpg" width="584" height="778" /></a>

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154233.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1196" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154233-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Pedestrians have to share the pavement with cyclists.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154216.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1195" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154216-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

A professional hitman with his wife.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154209.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1194" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154209-768x1024.jpg" width="584" height="778" /></a>

In Osaka, it is easy to tell which restaurants specialise in what food.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154190.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1241" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154190-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a> <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154202.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1242" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154202-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a> <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154203.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1243" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154203-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a> <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154205.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1244" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154205-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Didn't try this.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154175.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1245" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC154175-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Noodle bar.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC1541821.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1246" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC1541821-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Overall, we had a great time in Kyoto and Osaka. This was the first time I've been there and I would definitely not pass up an opportunity to return.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Only in Hong Kong</title>
		<link>http://www.phwl.org/blog/only-in-hong-kong/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 19 Dec 2013 05:16:25 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[phwl]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.phwl.org/blog/?p=1264</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[The below is a report of a true story. No names have been changed to protect identities.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/sherlockcsi-e1387429692390.jpg"><img alt="sherlockcsi" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/sherlockcsi-e1387429692390-768x1024.jpg" width="584" height="778" /></a>

<!--more-->

<strong>Previous day</strong>

We check into a very small serviced apartment in Mongkok.

<strong>Day of incident</strong>

0645 PL leaves for Tangxia.

0945 P and N leave the apartment.

1645 P returns.

1630 P discovers that cash has been taken from her luggage. Everything else, including her credit cards, passport, computer etc remain.

1647 P rings PL but he is not available to speak. Leaves message. Goes out to a scheduled appointment.

1923 PL calls P and is informed of the incident.

2111 PL returns to apartment. Finds that his carry-on, which was under the bed, has been tampered and document holder containing passport, credit cards and a thick load of RMB cash (reimbursement for an airfare) is missing. A more careful inspection reveals that the document holder had fallen from the lid of the carry-on under the bed.

2205 P returns.

2220 P rings Mongkok Police and gets put on hold for 10 minutes as they are busy. They suggest calling 999.

2230 P gets through and reports robbery.

2250 About 4 uniformed officers arrive at our 30 sq m unit. P explains what happens. Lots of walkie talkie action and note writing. Officer Wong asks other officers if they can lend their phone battery. An affirmative reply allows the investigation to proceed. Another 4 uniformed officers arrive. Some need to stand outside.  A more senior officer asks P the same questions. Two more plain clothes officers arrive.  We get some stools and watch the action from the kitchen. About 50 phone calls and CB conversations take place.

Officer Wong runs out of batteries again but since there are plenty of his colleagues around, he is able to replace his battery and continue the investigation. Officers radio for backup and the Criminal Investigation Department (CID). Place now looks like a murder scene from a TVB drama.

Our young, female neighbour arrives and pushes past the army of cops. I guess she is wondering what is going down.

2330 Officers squabble over who gets to ride in which police car. They are about as organised as a bunch of schoolgirls organising an outing. All leave except two who wait for the CID. One is older and stern looking. A stereotypical cop look. The other is younger, probably only recently started shaving. We discuss HK politics. Learn that the senior officer's son is a lifeguard who is planning to spend a year in Sydney on a working holiday.

Officers tell us about some of their jobs. For example, one person called the police when their hamburger was smaller than it appeared in the photo. Others have called to say that one shop ripped them off because another offered a lower price.

We tell them that in Sydney, cops spend most of their time at McDonalds since they get free meals there. Constables seriously discuss the possibility of moving to Sydney.

0030 Two detectives arrive, let's call them Sherlock and Watson. Sherlock is an amiable fellow dressed in a dapper fashion. Watson is younger and looks like one of those undercover cops who infiltrate triad gangs. P retells story, Sherlock furiously scribbling notes. I resist the temptation to ask him why doesn't he have a pipe. They decide to call in the fingerprint Crime Scene Investigation Department (CSI).

In the meantime, we discuss Hong Kong politics and police leave entitlements.

0133 CSI arrives to take fingerprints.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/csi.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1266" alt="csi" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/csi.jpg" width="584" height="782" /></a>

Fingerprints are found on the door but not on P's bag or wallet. Perpetrators must have used gloves. Fingerprints on door will be run through the CSI computer 0900 tomorrow.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/fingerprints-e1387429738498.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1265" alt="fingerprints" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/fingerprints-e1387429738498-768x1024.jpg" width="584" height="778" /></a>

More intense writing and phone calling takes place. During the breaks we find that CSI is very familiar with the drug situation in Cabramatta, Sydney and knows where to get the good heroin (opposite the railway station).

He will look at the closed circuit TV tapes but says unless the perp is recorded counting three foreign currencies in the lift, it is not likely to reveal anything. Sherlock says he thinks it is an inside job. Will interview the staff tomorrow.

In the end, we were extremely fortunate that they only took a little cash and left everything else. A new lock is being fitted to the apartment as I write. Overall it was a great drama to watch but the cost of the tickets was a bit high.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Girl in Hong Kong MTR</title>
		<link>http://www.phwl.org/blog/girl-in-hong-kong-mtr/</link>

	<item>
				<title>Hawkesbury River 2013</title>
		<link>http://www.phwl.org/blog/hawkesbury-river-2013/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 31 Dec 2013 05:11:55 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[phwl]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.phwl.org/blog/?p=1289</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Our trips to the Hawkesbury River have become an annual event (<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/hawkesbury-river-2012-2/">2012</a>, <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/hawkesbury-river-2011/">2011</a>).<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2844061.jpg"><img alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2844061-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

<!--more-->

As usual, the boat ramp was at capacity.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2743471.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1310" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2743471-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

<!--more-->

Went overboard with supplies, not much room for the passengers.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2743491.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1311" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2743491-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Warren at the campsite.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2843921.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1316" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2843921-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Campfire on the first night. <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2743671.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1313" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2743671-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Bandicoot hole, we saw it after dark but didn't get a photograph.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2843781.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1314" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2843781-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Cicada wing. The cicadas were really noisy and like an alarm clock set for the crack of dawn. Other insect life included ticks from which I received two bites.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2843941.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1317" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2843941-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

These were baked in foil for dinner on the first night. <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2743541.jpg"><img alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2743541-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

This trip, we had exceptional flathead fishing.  <a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2844121.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1320" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2844121-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

The biggest was around 50 cm.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2844131.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1321" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2844131-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Mulloway just short of the 45 cm minimum.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2844081.jpg"><img alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC2844081-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

On the way to the boat ramp at 6am to collect Barry for a day of fishing, our outboard started playing up and we had to restart about 10 times. Fortunately, we guessed that it was due to contaminated petrol and with a new tank, we were soon on our way. Unfortunately, that day, gale force winds were in place and the fishing was quiet. Fortunately, Barry managed to get this flattie.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC294417.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1322" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC294417-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Warren had the brilliant idea of putting the food in his tent so that animals wouldn't take it in the middle of the night. Something (probably a monitor lizard), made a hole in his tent and munched through half a loaf of bread. This photo shows the field repair in progress.<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC294423.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1323" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/PC294423-1024x768.jpg" width="584" height="438" /></a>

Another enjoyable trip but nothing really that wasn't covered previously. Although most of our catch were flathead, we also caught bream, mulloway, catfish and a stingray.

Our outboard is an Evinrude E30RLETA from 1993, still works beautifully but back at Warren's place, we broke the outboard's swivel bracket - another problem to fix!]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
				<title>Fishing with friends</title>
		<link>http://www.phwl.org/blog/fishing-with-friends/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 24 Apr 2014 22:13:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[phwl]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.phwl.org/blog/?p=1340</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Our boat was purchased around 1991 and has served us well. It is jointly owned with my close university friends, Beard and Warren. We were pleased to go out together for the first time in more than a decade. The first hour or so was disappointing, nothing much happened and I was wondering whether we were going to get skunked. However, a change of strategy brought us some luck and it turned into a great fishing day.

<a href="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/P4241279.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-1341" src="http://www.phwl.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/P4241279-1024x768.jpg" alt="OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA" width="584" height="438" /></a>]]></content:encoded>

		<wp:ping_status>closed</wp:ping_status>
